The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Saturday, October 04, 2003 				 Mice turn tasters
 Bangkok, Oct. 3 (Reuters):  Thailand is going to use mice to test food for poison before  it is served to President George W. Bush and 20 other Asia  Pacific leaders at a regional summit in Bangkok this month,  a top health official said today.																								Department of medical sciences chief Somsong Rugpao said samples of dishes served at the October 20-21 Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation summit would be injected into mice. Well have a result within a minute. If its safe, well tell waiters to start serving, he said. 
